  "text": "All five key multi-process architecture files were located in the local chromium checkout:\n\n1. **RenderProcessHostImpl** \u2014 `content/browser/renderer_host/render_process_host_impl.h` (line 195) / `.cc`. Browser-side representation of a renderer process; declared as `class CONTENT_EXPORT RenderProcessHostImpl`.\n\n2. **BrowserMainLoop** \u2014 `content/browser/browser_main_loop.h` (line 106) / `.cc`. The main browser-process event loop; declared as `class CONTENT_EXPORT BrowserMainLoop`.\n\n3. **RenderThreadImpl** \u2014 `content/renderer/render_thread_impl.h` (line 126) / `.cc`. The main thread of a renderer process; declared as `class CONTENT_EXPORT RenderThreadImpl`.\n\n4. **ChildProcessLauncher** \u2014 `content/browser/child_process_launcher.h` (line 212) / `.cc`. Responsible for spawning child (renderer, GPU, utility, etc.) processes; declared as `class CONTENT_EXPORT ChildProcessLauncher`.\n\n5. **content.mojom.Renderer** \u2014 `content/common/renderer.mojom` (line 49). The Mojo interface for browser-to-renderer communication, declared as `interface Renderer` in the `content.mojom` module. It includes methods like `CreateAgentSchedulingGroup` for setting up IPC channels.\n\nThe dependency chain flows: BrowserMainLoop starts the browser process \u2192 RenderProcessHostImpl manages renderer processes \u2192 ChildProcessLauncher spawns child processes \u2192 the content.mojom.Renderer Mojo interface enables IPC with the renderer \u2192 RenderThreadImpl runs the renderer-side main thread.",
